question: What is your comfort food on the campaign trail?
sanders: Last time out, we did a trip to the West Coast. And I gained three pounds in four days. So there’s too much comfort food.
harris: French fries. I love a good french fry, or a few, or many, or just the whole thing.
buttigieg: The word got out that I like beef jerky. And so people have been kind enough to give that to me on the road sometimes.
yang: Kind bars are my comfort food.
swalwell: It’s really comfort coffee. My favorite coffee is a mocha.
castro: I don’t have a comfort food. I have a comfort drink, which is iced tea.
gabbard: I try to stay away from it, but vegan cupcakes is probably a real threat on the trail.
bennet: Italian sausage sandwich at Pass Key in Pueblo, Colo.
inslee: It was M&M’s, but I’ve taken an oath now to lay off of the M&M’s to maintain belt security.
blasio: I think if I’ve got one go-to, it’s pulled pork.
hickenlooper: I do have a sweet tooth. And I will look for those little bowls of, you know, M&M’s or mints.
moulton: I mean, you can’t beat a burger for a quick classic American meal.
delaney: Grilled chicken sandwich from McDonald’s, no sauce. Two of them.
gillibrand: Glass of whiskey at the end of the night.
booker: When you’re a vegan, that means lots of veggies on the go.
